<headline>Rip Current Statement issued July 03 at 2:51PM CDT until July 03 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...HIGH RIP CURRENT RISK NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CDT THIS
EVENING...
* WHAT...Dangerous rip currents along Gulf facing beaches.
* WHERE...Matagorda Islands, Brazoria Islands, Galveston Island
and Bolivar Peninsula.
* WHEN...Until 9 PM CDT this evening.
* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water.</description>
<instruction>Swim near a lifeguard. If caught in a rip current, relax and
float. Don`t swim against the current. If able, swim in a
direction following the shoreline. If unable to escape, face the
shore and call or wave for help.</instruction>
